Song of the Year}}\n{{Latin Grammy Award for Record of the Year 2010s}}\n{{Premios Juventud for Voice of the Moment}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fonsi, Luis}}\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Singers from San Juan, Puerto Rico]]\n[[Category:Florida State University alumni]]\n[[Category:Latin Grammy Award winners]]\n[[Category:Latin pop singers]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican guitarists]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican male singers]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican singers]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican male soap opera actors]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican pop singers]]\n[[Category:Universal Music Latin Entertainment artists]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican male telenovela actors]]\n[[Category:Latin music songwriters]]\n[[Category:Dr. Phillips High School alumni]]\n[[Category:Guitarists from Florida]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican reggaeton artists]]\n[[Category:American male guitarists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American guitarists]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n", "name_user": "Pcgmsrich", "label": "safe", "comment": "cropped image", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luis_Fonsi"}
{"title_page": "Estelle discography", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2012}}\n{{Infobox artist discography\n|Artist          = [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]]\n|Image           = Estelle in Zac Posen.jpg\n|Caption         = \n|Studio          = 5\n|Singles         = 23\n|Option name     = Promotional singles\n|Option          = 6\n|EP              = 5\n|Music videos    = \n}}\n\nThe [[discography]] of [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]] consists of five studio albums, five extended plays, twenty-three singles (including nineteen as a featured artist), and six promotional singles.\n\nEstelle released her debut studio album ''[[The 18th Day]]''  on 18 October 2004 through [[V2 Records]], followed by a re-release 4 April 2005. The album peaked at number 35 on the [[UK Albums chart]]. It Includes the hit singles \"[[1980 (Estelle song)|1980]]\", \"[[Free (Estelle song)|Free]]\" and \"[[Go Gone]]\", all of which reached the Top 40 on the [[UK Singles Chart]].\n\nHer second studio album ''[[Shine (Estelle album)|Shine]]'' was released on 31 March 2008 through [[Atlantic Records]] and was preceded by the lead single \"[[Wait a Minute (Just a Touch)]]\" in November 2007. The album's second single, \"[[American Boy]]\", became a number one hit in the UK, as well as reaching the top 10 and receiving platinum status in many countries. It also earned Estelle her first three [[Grammy Award]] nominations (including [[Grammy Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]]) and won [[Grammy Award for Best Rap/Sung Collaboration|Best Rap/Sung Collaboration]]. \"American Boy\" was followed by her last song to reach the Top 40 in the UK to date, \"[[No Substitute Love]], and the singles \"[[Pretty Please (Love Me)]]\" and \"[[Come Over (Estelle song)|Come Over]]\" ''Shine'' has been [[British Phonographic Industry|certified Gold]] in the UK, as well peaking at number 6 in the UK and becoming her first and only album to chart internationally.\n\nEstelle followed ''Shine'' with ''[[All of Me (Estelle album)|All of Me]]'' on 28 February 2012, which featured the singles \"[[Freak (Estelle song)|Freak]]\", her last song to chart in the UK, \"[[Fall in Love (Estelle song)|Fall in Love]]\", the Grammy-nominated \"[[Thank You (Estelle song)|Thank You]]\", and \"[[Break My Heart (Estelle song)|Break My Heart]]\", the latter two charting in the top 40 of the US ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] chart.\n\nHer fourth studio album ''[[True Romance (Estelle album)|True Romance]]'' was released on 17 November 2015 through her own record label 1980 Recordings, as well as [[BMG Rights Management|BMG]]. Her song \"[[Conqueror (song)|Conqueror]]\" (originally a duet with [[Jussie Smollett]] from the American television show ''[[Empire (2015 TV series)|Empire]]'') peaked at number 42 in the United States.\n\nHer fifth studio album ''[[Lovers Rock (Estelle album)|Lovers Rock]]'' was released on 7 September 2018 through 1980 Records and VP Records, making it her first album as an independent artist. The album also marked a shift in Estelle's musical style from [[Pop music|pop]], [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]], and [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] to [[Reggae music|reggae]].\n\n==Studio albums==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of albums, with selected chart positions, sales, and certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:11em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"10\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Sales\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[UK Albums Chart|UK]]<br><ref name=uk>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/14047/estelle/|title=UK Charts > Estelle|publisher=[[Official Charts Company