essdate=6 August 2015}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"4\"|2015\n|[[3LAU]], Nom de Strip\n| ''Miami 2015''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"I'm Home\" \n|[[Obie Trice]] \n| ''[[The Hangover (Obie Trice album)|The Hangover]]''\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"Day Trippin\"\n|[[Kaskade]]\n| ''[[Automatic (Kaskade album)|Automatic]]''\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"Cylus\"\n|Serrio, Mizztamizzo\n| ''Ravennest''\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"Memory Of... (US)\"\n| 2016\n| [[De La Soul]]\n| ''[[And the Anonymous Nobody...]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"We are the Crystal Gems (Main Title)\"\n| rowspan=\"9\"|2017\n| [[Zach Callison]], [[Deedee Magno Hall]], & [[Michaela Dietz]]\n|rowspan=\"6\"| ''Steven Universe, Vol. 1 (Original Soundtrack)''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Steven and the Crystal Gems\"\n| Zach Callison, Deedee Magno Hall, & Michaela Dietz\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Stronger Than You\"\n|{{n/a}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"We are the Crystal Gems (Full Theme Song)\"\n| Zach Callison, Deedee Magno Hall, Michaela Dietz, [[Tom Scharpling]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Peace and Love on the Planet Earth\"\n| Zach Callison, Shelby Rabara, Deedee Magno Hall, Michaela Dietz\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Here Comes a Thought\"\n| [[AJ Michalka]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Murda\" \n| [[Cyhi the Prynce]] \n| ''[[No Dope on Sundays]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"U & I\"\n| [[Stokley Williams]]\n| ''Introducing Stokley''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Garden Shed\"\n| [[Tyler, the Creator]]\n| ''[[Flower Boy]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"For Just One Day Let's Only Thing About (Love)\"\n| rowspan=\"7\"| 2019\n| Zach Callison, Deedee Magno Hall, Michaela Dietz, Tom Scharpling, [[Shelby Rabara]], Uzo Aduba\n| ''Steven Universe, Vol. 2 (Original Soundtrack)''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Right Here\"\n| DJ Aktive, [[Freeway (rapper)|Freeway]] \n| ''The Tour''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Happily Ever After\"\n| Zach Callison, Deedee Magno Hall, Michaela Dietz, Tom Scharpling, Uzo Aduba, [[Jennifer Paz]], Shelby Rabara\n| rowspan=\"5\"| ''[[Steven Universe: The Movie#Music|Steven Universe the Music (Original Soundtrack)]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Other Friends\"\n| [[Sarah Stiles]], Zach Callison, Michaela Dietz\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Isn't It Love?\"\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"True Kinda Love\"\n| Zach Callison\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Finale\"\n| Zach Callison, Deedee Magno Hall, Michaela Dietz, Grace Rolek, Uzo Aduba, Jennifer Paz, Shelby Rabara, [[Kate Micucci]], [[Matthew Moy]], Tom Scharpling, & [[Toks Olagundoye]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Untrapped\" \n|2020\n| [[Yo Gotti]] \n|''Untrapped''\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=upper-alpha}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{Estelle}}\n\n[[Category:Discographies of British artists]]\n[[Category:Hip hop discographies]]\n[[Category:Rhythm and blues discographies]]\n[[Category:Soul music discographies]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2012}}\n{{Infobox artist discography\n|Artist          = [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]]\n|Image           = Estelle in Zac Posen.jpg\n|Caption         = \n|Studio          = 5\n|Singles         = 23\n|Option name     = Promotional singles\n|Option          = 6\n|EP              = 5\n|Music videos    = \n}}\n\nThe [[discography]] of [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]] consists of five studio albums, five extended plays, twenty-three singles (including nineteen as a featured artist), and six promotional singles.\n\nEstelle released her debut studio album ''[[The 18th Day]]''  on 18 October 2004 through [[V2 Records]], followed by a re-release 4 April 2005. The album peaked at number 35 on the [[UK Albums chart]]. It Includes the hit singles \"[[1980 (Estelle song)|1980]]\", \"[[Free (Estelle song)|Free]]\" and \"[[Go Gone]]\", all of which reached the Top 40 on the [[UK Singles Chart]].\n\nHer second studio ''[[Shine (Estelle album)|Shine]]'' was released on 31 March 2008 through [[Atlantic Records]] and was preceded by the lead single \"[[Wait a Minute (Just a Touch)]]\" in November 2007. The album's second single, \"[[American Boy]]\", became a number one hit in the UK, as well as reaching the top 10 and receiving platinum status in many countries. It also earned Estelle her first three [[Grammy Award]] nominations (including [[Grammy Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]]) and won [[Grammy Award for Best Rap/Sung Collaboration|Best Rap/Sung Collaboration]]. \"American Boy\" was followed by her last song to reach the Top 40 in the UK to date, \"[[No Substitute Love]], and the singles \"[[Pretty Please (Love Me)]]\" and \"[[Come Over (Estelle song)|Come Over]]\" ''Shine'' has been [[British Phonographic Industry|certified Gold]] in the UK, as well peaking at number 6 in the UK and becoming her first and only album to chart internationally.\n\nEstelle followed ''Shine'' with ''[[All of Me (Estelle album)|All of Me]]'' on 28 February 2012, which featured the singles \"[[Freak (Estelle song)|Freak]]\", her last song to chart in the UK, \"[[Fall in Love (Estelle song)|Fall in Love]]\", the Grammy-nominated \"[[Thank You (Estelle song)|Thank You]]\", and \"[[Break My Heart (Estelle song)|Break My Heart]]\", the latter two charting in the top 40 of the US ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] chart.\n\nHer fourth studio album ''[[True Romance (Estelle album)|True Romance]]'' was released on 17 November 2015 through her own record label 1980 Recordings, as well as [[BMG Rights Management|BMG]]. Her song \"[[Conqueror (song)|Conqueror]]\" (originally a duet with [[Jussie Smollett]] from the American television show ''[[Empire (2015 TV series)|Empire]]'') peaked at number 42 in the United States.\n\nHer fifth studio album ''[[Lovers Rock (Estelle album)|Lovers Rock]]'' was released on 7 September 2018 through 1980 Records and VP Records, making it her first album as an independent artist. The album also marked a shift in Estelle's musical style from [[Pop music|pop]], [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]], and [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] to [[Reggae music|reggae]].\n\n==Studio albums==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of albums, with selected chart positions, sales, and certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:11em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"10\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Sales\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[UK Albums Chart|UK]]<br><ref name=uk>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/14047/estelle/|title=UK Charts > Estelle|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=15 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[\u00d63 Austria Top 40|AUT]]<br><ref name=aut>{{cite web|url=http://www.austriancharts.at/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Estelle|title=Austrian Charts > Estelle|language=German|publisher=austriancharts.at Hung Medien|accessdate=9 July 2011}}</ref>\n\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|FRA]]<br><ref name=fra>{{cite web|url=http://lescharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Estelle|title=French Charts > Estelle|language=French|publisher=lescharts.com Hung Medien|accessdate=9 July 2011}}</ref>\n\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[GfK Entertainment Charts|GER]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://musicline.de/de/chartverfolgung_summary/artist/Estelle/?type=longplay|title=Chartverfolgung / Estelle / Longplay|language=German|publisher=musicline.de PhonoNet|accessdate=9 July 2011}}</ref>\n\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Irish Albums Chart|IRE]]<br><ref name=ire>{{cite web|url=http://irish-charts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Estelle|title=Irish Charts > Estelle|publisher=irish-charts.com Hung Medien|accessdate=9 July